Hi,every one.when i crawl bbs,i found a question,like this:
if i want to crawl www.examle.com/bbs/topic1.html,it have a lot of replies,and these replies  distribution in many pages,for example:
// url:www.examle.com/bbs/topic1.html
&lt;html&gt;
&lt;head&gt;
&lt;title&gt;topic&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
// topic context
// reply context(floor 1)
// reply context(floor2)
// ...
// reply context(flloor 100)

// &lt;a href=&#39;&#39;reply context (page 2)&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;
// &lt;a href=&quot;reply context(page 3)&quot;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;
// ...
// &lt;a href=&quot;reply context(page 100)&quot;&gt;100&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;

At the first time,we crawl this url(www.examle.com/bbs/topic1.html),and we can crawl all of its reply urls(&lt;a href=&#39;&#39;reply context (page 2)&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;,&lt;a href=&#39;&#39;reply context (page 3)&quot;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;)

but when we recrawl use heritrix,if the url(www.examle.com/bbs/topic1.html) had processed,and its etag(last-modified-time,length) and context md5 have not modified,so it will tell crawler that it do not need to recrawl.and it&#39;s reply pages(a href=&#39;&#39;reply context (page 2)&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;) will have no chance to recrawl.but when the url have new reply(it will find in the last reply url),we can not crawl it.

And now,i use this way to resolve this problem:
i store the url(www.examle.com/bbs/topic1.html)&#39;s last reply page url in database.and from this reply url to start recrawl.when i find have new reply page url,i will replace it.and the next time ,from the new reply url to start recrawl.

i do not know whether it is a good way to resove this problem,because it will maked a lot of change in Heritrix,any body have other way?




2011-03-10 



mickey.guoyun 

